args:
Having grown to adult size, Notte drives off the
fiends and the dragon, then opens the way to
the Faerie Kingdom. As the group finally arrives,
Nedrick makes his way to the Sacred Tree,
where he reveals his plan to use the Dawnshard
and swear a pact with the dragon Bahamut.
I look what? Wait, hold on a sec...
Okay, SERIOUSLY?! What is going ON\nwith my freakin' body today?!
Oh man, I feel super strong...
I think I can fight now!
She is taking on the enemy by herself—\nand she is WINNING.
No dumb dragon is gonna hurt my friends!
You there! Dragon! Stop it right now!
I no longer sense the savage mana that\nwas enraging the creature earlier.
Aw, you're not so bad, dragon...\nC'mere and get a belly rub!
She's treating the dragon like a puppy...
Oh, and you fiends and Templar dudes\ncan also bounce on outta here. Toodles!
I can't believe she just did that.
I sense an immense amount of mana...\nIs it all coming from Notte?
Forget us for a second—what the hell's\ngoin' on with yer body this time?!
All I know is that I wanted to fight\nalongside you all so bad, and then\nsuddenly...BLAMMO! I'm like this.
Although I STILL didn't open the way\nto the dang Faerie Kingdom...
I'm sure even the dragon could sense\nthe immense kindness in your heart.
You saved us, Notte. Thank you.
Oh man, I cannot TELL you how happy I\nwas to actually be useful for once.
Augh! It's the spooky voice guy again!
(Notte. It appears you have the ability to\ntemporarily draw upon your own future.)
Wait, so that's what's going on with this\nwhole ＂I'm an adult now＂ thing? Cool!\n...Er, but why is it happening now?
(I do not understand the particulars,\nbut only one with an abundance of mana\ncould possibly accomplish such a feat.)
(Notte, send my voice to your friends.\nWith the power you now possess,\nit should be a simple task.)
Uh, sure? Okay. So maybe like...this?
Hello, Gatov. Hello, Sheila. It has been\nsome time. And as for you...
I did not believe we would ever meet\nagain, {player_name}.
Of course. Now then, Notte, it is time\nfor you to finally open the way here.
Can you help us out once more, Notte?
Oh, you KNOW your girl has got you.
Step into the light, all of you.
An old pathway to the Faerie Kingdom,\njust as the historical document indicated.
It was a lot of trouble to use a sealing\nstone on that lake, but it was worth it!
And with a little ingenuity on this gate...\nYes, it should do nicely indeed.
The way to the Faerie Kingdom is as good\nas opened—and the Sacred Tree beckons!
So this is the Faerie Kingdom?
It's so WARM! I can't believe we were\njust hanging out on some snowy...
Wait, hang on—I'm tiny again!\nDude, boo! BOOOOOOO!
Man, that's a fast adolescence, huh?
I guess? Also, I'm more tired than the\nwheel of a cart—I think I used all my\npower getting that gate dealie open.
Maaan, this sucks. I thought I was finally\ngonna be able to help everybody.
Rest easy, Notte; there is still a great deal\nof mana issuing forth from your body.
Once you've recovered, you should be able\nto assume your larger form once more.
Now that you are safely arrived,\nthe time has come for me to tell all.
Notte? Sheila? Would you please\nbring everyone to me?
The two of you will know my location.
(I'm about to learn who I really am...)
Just believe in yourself, no matter what.\nOh, and don't lose your head.
(I came here of my own volition,\nand I can't back down now.)
So this is the Sacred Tree.
It seems to pierce the very heavens...
And I feel mana rolling off it in waves.
Sacred Shards are produced at the top,\nand the Dawnshard should be there\nas well.
Sacred Shards are fragments of the\npactstone upon which the Goddess Ilia and\nHolywyrm Elysium swore their allegiance.
You cannot ＂produce＂ new ones.\nIt is an impossibility.
So all the great stories of Alberia\nwould have you believe.
When we summit this great tree, you will\ncome to understand the truth for yourself.\nSo if you wish to be enlightened, follow.
Hold, Nedrick. Before I go further,\nI would understand your greater aim.
The Dawnshard is said to possess\npower enough to alter fate itself.
What do you desire with that power?\nWhat are you working to accomplish?
I once held a pact with a dragon;\nI now seek to forge that pact anew.
But what do you mean when you say you\nseek to ＂forge a pact anew?＂
The pact I swore with the dragon\nwas incomplete.
So I will obtain the Dawnshard\nand see it done right this time.
Once I do, the power of this revered\ndragon can be housed in my body.
And who is this mighty dragon\nthat you are sworn to?
